# Pew dbt model change overlay

Extends [agent-model-change](agent-model-change.mdc) for Pew Digital Data Mart (`ddm-dbt`).

## Grain and naming

- Page-level content grain: **`sitecore_item_id` + `date`** — exclude null / `(not set)` Sitecore IDs in content facts.
- Cast **`user_pseudo_id` to `varchar`** in GA4 raw staging; keep staging ↔ mart types aligned.
- Conventions: `dbt-conventions.mdc`

## High-risk areas

See `pew-dbt-high-risk.mdc`: `unique_key` on `fct_content_*` / `mart_content_*`, traffic source normalization, GA4 seed backfills (incident-specific scope only).

## Metrics and reporting

- GA4 content metrics: `ga4-metrics.mdc`
- For marts / reporting: row counts, metric totals, Looker exposures, `dashboard-support.mdc`
- Key content facts/marts: `fct_content_daily`, `mart_content_daily`, `mart_content_sources_daily`, and related content marts.

## Do not (Pew-specific)

- Generalize GA4 seed backfill fixes beyond their specific date/incident scope.
- Change `sitecore_item_id` filters or grain without mapping downstream content dashboards.

